== 霧的特性 ==
雾的本质是[[水汽|水汽]]凝结物。因此，只要空气温度达到或相当接近[[露点|露点]]，空气中的水汽就会凝结而生成雾。当气温高于[[冰点|冰点]]时，水汽凝结成液滴。当气温低于冰点时，水汽直接凝结为固态的冰晶，比如冰雾<ref name=":2" />。因为露点只受气温和[[湿度|湿度]]影响，所以雾的形成主要有两个原因<ref name="kepu_gen">{{cite web  | language =zh-hans  | publisher =中国科普博览  | title =雾的成因  | url =http://www.kepu.net.cn/gb/earth/weather/water/wtr013.html  | author =  | date =  | accessdate =2009-04-05  | archive-date =2021-02-04  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20210204050207/http://www.kepu.net.cn/gb/earth/weather/water/wtr013.html  | dead-url =no  }}</ref>：一是空气中的水汽大量增加，使得濕度升高至露點，从而形成雾，比如蒸汽雾和锋面雾；二是气温下降至低于露点而生成雾，比如平流雾和辐射雾。

雾和[[云|云]]的不同在于，云生成于大气的高层，而雾接近地表。

霧和降雨也有關聯。當霧中的小雲滴會開始凝聚，一旦重量增加空氣支持不住。就會產生[[降水|降水]]。霧的降水型態通常為[[毛毛雨|毛毛雨]]或非常小的[[雪|雪]]。雲中小水滴凝聚的主要原因可能為霧層遇到地形被抬升或是上下方空氣移動、強制壓縮霧層。當大氣溫度低於[[熔点|冰點]]時，毛毛雨會結凍，變成冰晶<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/451519005|title=Enchanted Rock - A Natural and Human History|last=Allred|first=Lance|date=2009|publisher=University of Texas Press|year=|isbn=9780292799332|edition=1st ed|location=Austin, TX|pages=99|chapter=Enchanted Rock : a natural and human history|oclc=451519005}}</ref>。

== 霧的成因 ==
[[File:FogParticlesHighSpeed.jpg|右]]
霧通常發生在[[相對濕度|相對溼度]]接近100％時，有時也有機會在較低濕度時產生<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/744303838|title=Agroecology: The Ecology of Sustainable Food Systems, Third Edition|last=Gliessman|first=Stephen R.|publisher=CRC Press|year=2014|isbn=9781439895610|edition=Third edition|location=Boca Raton|pages=73|chapter=Agroecology : the ecology of sustainable food systems|oclc=744303838}}</ref>。一般霧在當[[露点|露點溫度]]與空氣溫度的差異在2°C以下時產生<ref name=":2" />。當溫度條件達到，水蒸氣結成為懸浮在空氣中的微小液態水滴時，如果形成的位置靠近人類生活的地域，就會被稱為霧<ref name="convection">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=QECy_UBdyrcC&pg=PA66|title=Meteorology at the Millennium|author=Pearce|first=Robert Penrose|publisher=Academic Press|accessdate=2018-12-23|year=2002|isbn=9780125480352|location=Cambridge, MA, USA|page=66|pages=|language=en-gb}}</ref>。

至於一開始水蒸氣為什麼能夠被加入到空氣中，則是霧的科學中相當重要的研究課題。以下是四種水蒸氣產生的例子：

# [[降水|降水]]或是降落至地面的[[幡狀雲|幡狀雲]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrh.noaa.gov/otx/outreach/ttalk/virga.php|title=Virga and Dry Thunderstorms|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=National Weather Service Office, Spokane, Washington|date=|year=2009|publisher=|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090522112015/http://www.wrh.noaa.gov/otx/outreach/ttalk/virga.php|archivedate=2009-05-22|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref>
# 因為白天[[太阳|太陽]]加熱，從[[海|海洋]]，[[湖泊|湖泊]]或水體蒸發出來的水<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knmi.nl/~hurkvd/Loco_workshop/Workshop_report.pdf|title=Global maps of Local Land-Atmosphere coupling|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=|date=2008-06-27|year=|publisher=KNMI|language=en-us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090225074154/http://www.knmi.nl/~hurkvd/Loco_workshop/Workshop_report.pdf|archivedate=25 February 2009|author1=Bart van den Hurk|author2=Eleanor Blyth|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>
# 植物的蒸散作用<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gsfc.nasa.gov/topstory/20020926landcover.html|title=Landcover changes may rival greenhouse gases as cause of climate change|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=|date=2002-10-01|year=|publisher=National Aeronautics and Space Administration Goddard Space Flight Center|language=en-us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603022239/http://www.gsfc.nasa.gov/topstory/20020926landcover.html|archivedate=2008-06-03|author1=Krishna Ramanujan|author2=Brad Bohlander}}</ref>
# 冷空氣或乾空氣移動到溫暖水域上空<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.srh.weather.gov/srh/jetstream/synoptic/airmass.htm|title=Air Masses|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=National Weather Service JetStream|date=|year=2008|publisher=|language=en-us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224062959/http://www.srh.weather.gov/srh/jetstream/synoptic/airmass.htm|archivedate=2008-12-24|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>

水蒸氣通常開始凝結在[[云凝结核|凝結核]]上，例如[[灰塵|灰塵]]、[[冰晶|冰晶]]和空氣中的[[盐_(化学)|鹽]]，以形成雲和霧<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amsglossary.allenpress.com/glossary/search?id=front1|title=Front|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=|date=June 2000|work=Glossary of Meteorology|publisher=American Meteorological Society|language=en-us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121209205818/http://amsglossary.allenpress.com/glossary/search?id=front1|archivedate=2012-12-09|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref><ref name="DR">{{cite web|url=http://www.wpc.ncep.noaa.gov/sfc/UASfcManualVersion1.pdf|title=Unified Surface Analysis Manual|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=David M. Roth|date=2005-11-17|publisher=Hydrometeorological Prediction Center|language=en-us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060929004553/http://www.hpc.ncep.noaa.gov/sfc/UASfcManualVersion1.pdf|archivedate=2006-09-29|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref>。與[[层云|層雲]]一樣，霧是一個穩定的雲層<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zamg.ac.at/docu/Manual/SatManu/main.htm?/docu/Manual/SatManu/CMs/FgStr/backgr.htm|title=Fog And Stratus – Meteorological Physical Background|accessdate=2018-12-23|author=FMI|date=|year=2007|publisher=Zentralanstalt für Meteorologie und Geodynamik|language=en-gb|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706085616/http://www.zamg.ac.at/docu/Manual/SatManu/main.htm?%2Fdocu%2FManual%2FSatManu%2FCMs%2FFgStr%2Fbackgr.htm|archivedate=2011-07-06|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref>。
